@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="col-lg-9 mx-auto">
    <p class="bey-eyebrow bey-eyebrow-muted mb-2">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="display-6 fw-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-secondary small mb-4">Last updated: 10 May 2026</p>

    <p class="lead text-secondary">
        BEY HR (“we”, “us”) explains how we collect, use, and protect personal information when you use our talent and recruitment platform
        (the “Services”). By using BEY HR, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-5">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-3">
            BEY HR is operated as a demonstration and university project focused on HR technology. Where this policy refers to contact details,
            you can reach us through the information on our <a asp-action="Contact" asp-controller="Home">Contact</a> page.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">2. Information we collect</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-2">We may process the following categories of information, depending on how you use the Services:</p>
        <ul class="text-secondary">
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Account data:</strong> name, email address, username, role (for example candidate, company, or administrator), and authentication details.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Profile and application data:</strong> CVs, cover letters, education and work history, languages, certificates, photos you choose to upload, and messages you submit with an application.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Employer and job data:</strong> company profile information, job descriptions, and recruitment decisions you record in the product.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device identifiers, timestamps, and similar diagnostics needed to operate and secure the site.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">3. How we use your information</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-2">We use personal information to:</p>
        <ul class="text-secondary">
            <li class="mb-2">Provide accounts, dashboards, job listings, applications, and related features;</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Allow employers to evaluate applications submitted to their vacancies and communicate outcomes;</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Maintain security, detect abuse, troubleshoot errors, and improve performance;</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Comply with applicable law or respond to lawful requests where required.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="hrm-card p-4 mt-3 bey-section-card">
            <p class="mb-0 text-secondary">
                We do not sell your personal information. Marketing use, if introduced later, would be described in an updated policy and, where required, with your consent.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">4. Sharing of information</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-2">
            When you apply to a job, the employer that posted the role may access the application materials and profile information you submitted for that process.
            Administrators of the platform may access data as needed to operate the system, support users, and enforce rules.
        </p>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            We may use hosting, email, or analytics providers who process data on our instructions under appropriate agreements. Those providers are chosen to support the security of the Services.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">5. Retention and deletion</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            We keep information only as long as necessary for the purposes above, unless a longer period is required by law.
            Signed-in users may have options to delete their account or withdraw application data depending on features enabled in the product;
            employers may retain records according to their own legal obligations once data has been shared with them as part of a hiring process.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">6. Security</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            We implement reasonable technical and organisational measures suited to an educational/demo deployment, including access controls where the product supports them.
            No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure; you share information at your own risk beyond what we can reasonably protect.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">7. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            We may use cookies or local storage required for sign-in sessions, security (for example anti-forgery tokens), and basic preferences.
            You can control cookies through your browser settings; disabling essential cookies may prevent parts of the site from working correctly.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">8. International transfers</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            Information may be processed on servers located in Türkiye or other regions supported by our hosting environment.
            If data moves across borders, we take steps aligned with applicable data protection expectations for our context.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">9. Your rights</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-2">
            Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal information, or to object to certain processing.
            To exercise rights for data we control, contact us via the details on our <a asp-action="Contact" asp-controller="Home">Contact</a> page.
        </p>
        <p class="text-secondary small mb-0">
            Demo projects may expose limited tooling; practical availability of self-service deletion features is described where implemented in the application.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4 mb-5">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3 hrm-section-title">10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
            We may update this Privacy Policy when our practices change. Material changes may be communicated through the site or your account email when available.
            Continued use of BEY HR after updates means you accept the revised policy.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
